      <question>2.设f(x)在[0,1]上二阶可导，且<latex>f(0)=\frac{1}{2} ,f(\frac{1}{2} )=1,f(1)=0</latex>.证明：
      </question>
      <img src="question">5.2.png</img>
      <quiz>
        <id>1</id>
        <content>(1)<latex>\exists \zeta \in (0,1)</latex>,使得<latex>f^{'}(\zeta )=0</latex>.（4分）  </content>
        <img src="question">5.2.1.png</img>
        <ans>证：由题意f(x)在[0,1]连续.由介值定理，
        <latex>\exists \zeta \in (0,1),s.t.f(\xi  )=\frac{1}{2}</latex>.
        由于f(x)在[0,1]可导，<latex>f(0)=\frac{1}{2},f(\xi  )=\frac{1}{2}.</latex>
        由Rolle定理，<latex>\exists \zeta  \in (0,\xi  )\subset (0,1)</latex>，使得<latex>f^{'}(\zeta  )  =0</latex>.
        </ans>
      </quiz>
     <quiz>
        <id>2</id>
        <content>(2)<latex>\exists \eta \in (0,1) </latex>，使得<latex>f^{''}(\eta )(1-\eta )-2f^{'}(\eta )=0</latex>.</content>
        <img src="question">5.2.2.png</img>
        <ans>
        令<latex>F(x)=f^{'}(x)(1-x)^2</latex>，显然F(x)在[0,1]可导，
        且<latex>F(1)=0,F(\zeta )=0.</latex>由Rolle定理，
        <latex>\exists \zeta \in (0,\zeta )\subset (0,1)</latex>，使得<latex>F^{'}(\eta )=0</latex>，
        即<latex>f^{'}(\eta  )(1-\eta  )-2f^{'}(\eta   )=0</latex>.
        </ans>
     </quiz>
